cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the evaluation of adversarial defenses in machine learning and computer vision, which are topics covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper proposes a new ensemble of attacks to test the robustness of machine learning models. The second most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), as the paper applies the ensemble to over 40 computer vision models. The third likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with adversarial attacks and defenses. The fourth likely category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), as the paper deals with machine learning models and their vulnerabilities. The fifth likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as the paper deals with attacks and defenses against neural networks.
